What are the main requirements
for websites and app owners?

   [wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw==] Policy_150

Privacy and Cookie Policy

   Provide a Privacy and Cookie Policy that also includes any third party
   service providers you're using, like Google Analytics or Google
   Adsense.

   [wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw==] Cookie_150

EU Cookie Law

   If you have users from the EU, you must display a cookie banner,
   provide a cookie policy, acquire consent for the installation of
   cookies and block profiling cookies until consent has been obtained.

   [wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw==] Terms_150

Terms and Conditions

   Terms and Conditions set the terms for how your site, app or service
   must be used and, most importantly, protect you from potential
   liabilities.

   [wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw==] Acquire_consent

GDPR Consent Records

   If you have EU-based users and you use web-forms on your site — such as
   newsletter sign-up forms or registration forms — you must collect and
   maintain valid records of consent in order for the consent you’ve
   collected to be considered valid.

   [wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICRAEAOw==] Fr

"Is France covered?"

   Our legal text is modeled after the strictest privacy requirements
   found in the world like the GDPR, the US's CalOPPA and Australia's
   APPs. France is one of the countries our legal team monitors more
   closely; we regularly check the major privacy laws and other relevant
   EU Member State legislations to ensure that our solutions meet all
   necessary requirements.
